      "page_number": 1,
      "raw_text": "BOISE, July 16.-Impeachment\nOf all witnesses who alleged Or\nchard was not present at the blow\ning up Of the Bunker Hill & Sulli-\nvan mill and recital Of Cripple\nCreek conditions covered this\nmornings session in the Haywood\ntrial. Nothing new was brought\nout.\n\n\nA. Tholman, former president Of\nthe Mine Owners association of\nCripple Creek, testified that Nc\nCormick and Beck were killed in\nthe Vindicator mine by bomb. He\nexplained how Orchard got into the\nmine and why he made a mistake\nin the levels. Otherwise his testi-\nmony was unimportant.\n\n\nThe state arrested another wit\nness for the defense who contra\ndicted Orchards story yesterday.\nc. w. Aller, formerly ticket\nagent in the Cripple Creek district,\nwas taken in custody on the charge\nof perjury."
    }
